headline: Citizens Survey Finds Young Adults Redefining Success and How to Achieve It, as Anxiety About the Future Mounts
summary: PROVIDENCE, R.I., October 30, 2025--Young adults are thinking about success in dramatically different ways than previous generations, with more than half (57%) reporting that money is affecting their mental health, only a quarter (26%) aspiring to climb the corporate ladder, and fewer than 40% believing they will be more successful than their parents, according to a Citizens survey released today.
